### Data Fetching

⚠️ **Currently no API layer** - uses static/mock data
✅ **When adding API calls**, create `src/services/` or `src/api/` folder
✅ **Use `fetch` or `axios`** (axios not installed yet)
✅ **Handle loading and error states** with `useState`

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Future API pattern
const [data, setData] = useState([]);
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
const [error, setError] = useState(null);

useEffect(() => {
  async function fetchData() {
    try {
      const response = await fetch('/api/data');
      const result = await response.json();
      setData(result);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err);
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  }
  fetchData();
}, []);
```

