## Section E: Component Creation Rules

### Template for New Component

```typescript
// src/components/ui/mycomponent/MyComponent.tsx
import { ReactNode } from "react";

interface MyComponentProps {
  // Required props first
  title: string;
  // Optional props with defaults
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary";
  children?: ReactNode;
  className?: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}

const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({
  title,
  variant = "primary",
  children,
  className = "",
  onClick,
}) => {
  return (
    <div className={`base-styles ${variant}-styles ${className}`}>
      <h2>{title}</h2>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};

export default MyComponent;
```

### Required File Structure
1. **Import statements** (React, types, other components)
2. **Interface definition** for props
3. **Component definition** with React.FC
4. **Default export**

### Prop Validation
✅ **Use TypeScript interfaces** (not PropTypes)
✅ **Mark optional props with `?`**
✅ **Provide default values** in destructuring
✅ **Use union types** for variants: `"primary" | "secondary"`

### Export Pattern
✅ **Default export for components**: `export default Button;`
✅ **Named exports for hooks/utilities**: `export { useModal };`
✅ **Named exports for multiple items**: Icons in `src/icons/index.ts`

