## Section L: Critical Rules (Don'ts)

### What Files Should Never Be Modified
❌ **`vite.config.ts`** - Only modify if adding new plugins
❌ **`tsconfig.json`** - Only modify if changing TypeScript settings
❌ **`postcss.config.js`** - Only modify if changing PostCSS config
❌ **`package.json`** - Only modify when adding/removing dependencies
❌ **`index.css` theme variables** - Only modify for theme changes, not for component-specific styles

### What Patterns to Avoid
❌ **Don't create separate CSS files** for components (use Tailwind)
❌ **Don't use class components** (use functional components)
❌ **Don't use PropTypes** (use TypeScript interfaces)
❌ **Don't import from "react-router-dom"** (use "react-router")
❌ **Don't forget dark mode variants** in styles
❌ **Don't use inline styles** (use Tailwind classes)
❌ **Don't create global state** without Context (use existing contexts or create new one)

### Security Considerations
✅ **Never commit API keys** or secrets to code
✅ **Use environment variables** for sensitive data
✅ **Validate user input** in forms
✅ **Sanitize data** before rendering (if from external sources)

### Performance Considerations
✅ **Use `React.memo`** for expensive components (if needed)
