## Summary of Key Patterns

### ✅ DO
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Use React.FC type annotation
- Define props interfaces above component
- Use default exports for components
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Include dark mode variants
- Use React Context for global state
- Use `useState` for local state
- Import from "react-router" (not "react-router-dom")
- Use PascalCase for component files
- Use camelCase for variables
- Always include PageMeta in pages
- Use relative imports (`../`, `../../`)

### ❌ DON'T
- Create separate CSS files for components
- Use class components
- Use PropTypes (use TypeScript)
- Import from "react-router-dom"
- Forget dark mode variants
- Use inline styles
- Create global state without Context
- Modify config files unnecessarily

